# Example authorized_keys for the shared `rsx-tui` SSH user.
#
# One line per registered trader. `restrict` denies everything (port /
# agent / X11 forwarding, user-rc, and pty); `pty` re-adds the terminal
# the full-screen ratatui app needs; `command=` forces this key's own
# rsx-tui session and ignores whatever the client asked to run. The user
# id after the dispatch path is that key's RSX_TUI_USER — the only thing
# that varies per line. See specs/2/54-tui-access.md.
#
# Manage with: rsx-tui-authorize add <user_id> <pubkey> <comment>
#
# Format:
#   restrict,pty,command="/usr/local/bin/rsx-tui-dispatch <user_id>" <pubkey> <comment>

restrict,pty,command="/usr/local/bin/rsx-tui-dispatch 42" ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIexampleAliceKeyxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx trader-alice
restrict,pty,command="/usr/local/bin/rsx-tui-dispatch 7" ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIexampleBobKeyxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx trader-bob
